================================================================================
BULK IMAGE PROCESSING & ANALYSIS PROMPT
================================================================================

TASK: Process 5-6 WhatsApp screenshot images autonomously

SETUP:
- Images are in current directory named like:
  * WhatsApp Image 2026-03-01 at 10.10.21 AM.jpeg
  * WhatsApp Image 2026-03-02 at 15.45.33 PM.jpeg
  [etc]

ACTIONS TO PERFORM:

1. AUTO-RECOGNIZE PATTERN
   - Parse filename timestamps (extract date & time)
   - Group images by date
   - Flag if any are duplicates or near-duplicates

2. ANALYZE CONTENT
   - Extract text from each image (OCR if needed)
   - Categorize content type (screenshot, chart, diagram, conversation, etc)
   - Identify any data, tables, or structured information
   - Flag sensitive information (if any)

3. METADATA GENERATION
   - Create JSON metadata file: image_metadata.json
   - Include: filename, timestamp, content_type, extracted_text, analysis
   - Example structure:
     {
       "images": [
         {
           "filename": "WhatsApp Image 2026-03-01 at 10.10.21 AM.jpeg",
           "timestamp": "2026-03-01T10:10:21",
           "content_type": "screenshot|chart|conversation|diagram",
           "extracted_text": "...",
           "analysis": "...",
           "is_sensitive": false
         }
       ]
     }

4. CREATE SUMMARY REPORT
   - Total images processed: N
   - Date range: YYYY-MM-DD to YYYY-MM-DD
   - Content breakdown (types)
   - Key findings or insights
   - Save as: image_analysis_report.txt

5. OPTIONAL: CREATE DATASET SCHEMA
   If images contain data tables/charts:
   - Extract structured data
   - Generate CSV if applicable
   - Create data dictionary

6. OUTPUT STRUCTURE
   Create ./processed_images/ directory with:
   ├── image_metadata.json
   ├── image_analysis_report.txt
   └── extracted_data.csv (if applicable)

DO NOT modify or rename original images.
DO preserve all original files.
================================================================================

CLAUDE CLI COMMAND:
claude code --upload-glob "*.jpeg" --auto-recognize-type --context "Process WhatsApp screenshot images - extract timestamps, analyze content, generate metadata JSON and summary report"

OR if uploading manually:
1. In Claude app, attach all 5-6 images
2. Run this prompt
3. Claude will auto-process and output results
